World War. Critics praised his poetry for its accessibility, even in translation.<sup id=\"cite_ref-nyt_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Tomas_Transtr%C3%B6mer#cite_note-nyt-2\"><span>[<\/span>2<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup> His poetry has been translated into over 60 languages.<sup id=\"cite_ref-nyt_2-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Tomas_Transtr%C3%B6mer#cite_note-nyt-2\"><span>[<\/span>2<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup> He was the recipient of the 1990 <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Neustadt_International_Prize_for_Literature\" title=\"Neustadt International Prize for Literature\">Neustadt International Prize for Literature<\/a> and the 2011 <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Nobel_Prize_in_Literature\" title=\"Nobel Prize in Literature\">Nobel Prize in Literature<\/a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-ap_nobel_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Tomas_Transtr%C3%B6mer#cite_note-ap_nobel-5\"><span>[<\/span>5<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><\/p>","name":"Tomas Transtr\u00f6mer","place_of_birth":"Stockholm","place_of_death":null,"text":"Tomas Transtr\u00f6mer , Literature, 2011","year":2011.0}